    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-03-30T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-03-30T13:00:00-05:00" n="275"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d275">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72111N83/50</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Norway</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SAG1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Schmedeman</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Christiania</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-03-30T19:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 30, 1918—7 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received March 31, 1.46 a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>624. My telegram No. 576, March 9, 7 p.m. French, British and Italian Ministers
                    here have received instructions to acknowledge note of March 9 from Norwegian
                    Minister for Foreign Affairs and in doing so to state that their respective
                    Governments regard said note as signifying “that the Norwegian Government will
                    not only maintain its neutrality but also its rights as a neutral.”</p>
                <p>My Allied colleagues are deferring carrying out their instructions until I am
                    authorized to take similar action. I [acknowledged] the receipt of the Norwegian
                    note without comment on March 18.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SAG1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Schmedeman</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
